title: Two Zionist warplanes intercepted by Hezbollah » Iraqi News Agency
text: Follow-up - INA The Lebanese Hezbollah announced, today, Thursday, that it had confronted two Zionist warplanes in the south of the country. The party said in a statement, "In support of our steadfast Palestinian people in the Gaza Strip and support of their valiant and honourable resistance, and in defense of Lebanon and its people, the air defense units of the Islamic Resistance today, Thursday 09-26-2024, confronted two hostile warplanes coming from the sea towards Adloun with air defense weapons and forced them to leave Lebanese airspace."
